<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>I think they are resisting the idea of rewriting combat system for PvP. (NT)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Min">Min</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:01 a.m. 26/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> I think they are resisting the idea of rewriting combat system for PvP. (NT)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1181" TARGET=_self>**Topic** EQ pvp should not be all level based</A> (DarkHelm Da Bad of CC)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> I was fairly disapointed after reading what Geoferry Zatkin had

<BR>&gt; to say below.
<P>&gt; New info from Geoffrey Z on EQ PvP
<P>&gt; Posted By: TheBlack[BCK]
<P>&gt; Posted On: 7:31 p.m. 24/2/1999
<P>&gt; Subject: New info from Geoffrey Z on EQ PvP
<P>&gt; Oh. There is a TINY (like 1-2% out of 100) bonus added on for
<P>&gt; people a level to three above you for resistances. Quite
<BR>&gt; possibly it is the
<P>&gt; fact that they higher level people have better equipment, or
<BR>&gt; have defensive
<P>&gt; spells up on them.
<P>&gt; Our system is heavily based on skills. Giving somebody a flaming
<P>&gt; avenger at first level just won't do much to help them - they
<BR>&gt; don't have the
<P>&gt; skill to use it. Level, which sets your skill caps, is very
<BR>&gt; important. A
<P>&gt; 6th level guy can probably take out two level 4's. A 30th level
<BR>&gt; guy can
<P>&gt; probably take out two level 24-25's. That is how all the combat
<BR>&gt; equations
<P>&gt; have been written, and how we have balanced game play.
<P>&gt; Superior weapons and equipment will help - a level 25 with
<BR>&gt; equipment
<P>&gt; could take out a level 30 if the level 30 was naked, or in poor
<BR>&gt; equipment.
<P>&gt; But two equally-equipped equally-skilled warriors of level 25
<BR>&gt; and 30? The
<P>&gt; 30 would win. Hands down in a one on one fight.
<P>&gt; For casters it is a little different - the spells they use make
<BR>&gt; all
<P>&gt; the difference. But yes, the guy 2 levels above you will save a
<BR>&gt; bit better.
<P>&gt; Unless she has a resist fire and you huck a fire bolt at her -
<BR>&gt; then she will
<P>&gt; save a lot better.
<P>&gt; Geoffrey C. Zatkin
<P>&gt; Arch-Magi of Norrath
<P>&gt; I think it is in full agreement with everyone who PvPs this is
<BR>&gt; not what we want. We want it so a lvl 25 has a fair chance to
<BR>&gt; take out a level 30 and so on. Pvping just is not as fun if it
<BR>&gt; is all level based. The fact a lvl 30 can take out two level
<BR>&gt; 24s, TWO people who are a mere 5-6 levels below him is
<BR>&gt; ludicrous. Whats the point of having this +-4 level pk window
<BR>&gt; thing if you cannot kill anyone higher then you? Pking is a lot
<BR>&gt; more viable and fun when it is based on skill. Yes a lvl 29
<BR>&gt; should have an advantage over a level 25. Not a huge advantage,
<BR>&gt; but a slight one, basically the amount of hitpoints each has and
<BR>&gt; that should be it. It is kind of a bummer when you know you are
<BR>&gt; not gonna be able to take someone who is 4 levels above you
<BR>&gt; regardless at how good at pvping you are compared to him. Its
<BR>&gt; not cool that the guy who spends the most time killing monsters
<BR>&gt; is the best at pvping just because of his level. I do not think
<BR>&gt; it is too late to change any of us, but judging by Zatkin's
<BR>&gt; statement above I am sorry to say I do not think anything will
<BR>&gt; be done about this, just because of the relative smallness of
<BR>&gt; the pvp community in eq.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
